{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram — Checkout pincode mismatch warning config (Phase 2.11E — Requirement B).

  Publishes window.GanguramPincodeMismatchConfig (the logged-in customer's SAVED
  address pincodes — the ones Shopify prefills at checkout) and loads
  assets/ganguram-pincode-mismatch.js (window.GanguramPincodeMismatch). The module
  warns IN THE CART when the delivery-checker pincode (ganguram_selected_pincode)
  matches none of those saved pincodes.

  SHOPIFY LIMITATION: a standard theme cannot read the pincode TYPED on Shopify's
  hosted checkout, so the exact checkout comparison needs a Checkout UI Extension
  (app); the cart attribute ganguram_selected_pincode (Phase 2.11D.2) is provided
  for it. For a guest (no saved address) the array is empty -> no warning (fail-open).
  See docs/delivery-rule-engine-admin-setup.md §7.

  Warning only — never blocks checkout. The warning wording lives in the message
  catalog (CHECKOUT_PINCODE_MISMATCH / _SHORT). Set useLong:true for the long copy.
  No checkout / shipping / ShipZip / SBZ / zipLogic / resolver / settings_data change.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramPincodeMismatchConfig = {
    enabled: true,
    useLong: false,
    savedPincodes: [
      {%- if customer -%}
        {%- for address in customer.addresses -%}
          {{ address.zip | default: '' | json }}{%- unless forloop.last -%},{%- endunless -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    ]
  };
</script>
{{ 'ganguram-pincode-mismatch.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-pincode-mismatch.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
